                             <img alt="" class="img-responsive rsp-img-center" src="http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Celebrity-Hairstylists-Share-Their-Top-Haircare-Tools-Products.jpg">                                                                                 </div><!-- Media Finish -->
                                                <div class="post-text clearfix">
                            <p>Whenever we see celebrities on the red carpet, their hair is always styled to perfection. Whether they go for straight and sleek or loose and glamorous, there is a hair stylist to give the last magical touch. But it isn&#8217;t all just a talented pair of hands. Celebrity hairstylists have a set of tools that help create their clients&#8217; desired looks. So when we had the chance to hang out with Antonio Papa, Lourd Ramos, and Jonathan Velasco—who have just been named Denman&#8217;s first Filipino ambassadors—we asked them to share the top hair styling tools and products that always have their back.</p>
<p>Scroll down below to find out:</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-33360" src="http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Antonio-Papa-Top-Hair-Products.jpg" alt="Antonio-Papa-Top-Hair-Products" width="500" height="615" srcset="http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Antonio-Papa-Top-Hair-Products-244x300.jpg 244w, http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Antonio-Papa-Top-Hair-Products-768x945.jpg 768w, http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Antonio-Papa-Top-Hair-Products-832x1024.jpg 832w, http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Antonio-Papa-Top-Hair-Products-740x911.jpg 740w, http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Antonio-Papa-Top-Hair-Products.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;First one is the Denman DCR2 brush. It gives volume and since it&#8217;s ceramic, it retains the heat from the blow dryer and makes styling faster and easier. Next is the thickening spray from Bumble &amp; Bumble. It gives texture to your strands and instantly volumizes hair. Plus, it smells good. I also love the surf spray from Bumble &amp; Bumble if you want nice beach waves. Then, of course to fix, hair sprays from Philip B. and Oribe.&#8221;- <strong>Antonio Papa</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-33359" src="http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Lourd-Ramos-Top-Hair-Products.jpg" alt="Lourd-Ramos-Top-Hair-Products" width="500" height="687" srcset="http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Lourd-Ramos-Top-Hair-Products-768x1056.jpg 768w, http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Lourd-Ramos-Top-Hair-Products-745x1024.jpg 745w, http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Lourd-Ramos-Top-Hair-Products-740x1017.jpg 740w, http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Lourd-Ramos-Top-Hair-Products.jpg 771w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;I love the Tresemme Keratin Smooth Heat Protection Spray and lotion because it protects and shields the hair from heat and thermal usage. It makes your hair look flawless. I also like to use the mousse from Tresemme because it creates volume and you can also use it for a wet look effect if you want to look a little more formal. The Davines N10 and N7 wax which is a liquid wax and a forming matte wax because I like to restructure hair according to the feeling and emotion of my client. Another favorite is the Ol Oil with Roucou oil from Davines because it makes your hair shinier and look less damaged. You can actually put 1 teaspoon of the oil in your favorite conditioner and it becomes a very good treatment that you can use once a month. I always have my Denman skeleton brush because it can produce volume, it can make your hair straight, it can make your hair fly away, you can re-comb gelled hair, you can use this with dye, you can use it with curls because it&#8217;s really soft. It&#8217;s my ultimate, universal brush.&#8221;- <strong>Lourd Ramos</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-33358" src="http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Jonathan-Velasco-Top-Hair-Products.jpg" alt="Jonathan-Velasco-Top-Hair-Products" width="500" height="645" srcset="http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Jonathan-Velasco-Top-Hair-Products-740x955.jpg 740w, http://www.starstyle.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Jonathan-Velasco-Top-Hair-Products.jpg 758w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;I always use the classic Denman brush, that&#8217;s my favorite because it&#8217;s versatile. You can use it to make straight and curly hair as well as if you want to create volume. For hair products, I usually use Aveda Air Control Hair Spray to add volume and the style-prep products before blow drying to protect the hair from heat damage. That&#8217;s it. I don&#8217;t like to overuse products especially with out kind of weather.&#8221;- <strong>Jonathan Velasco</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
